data.title: Fitness Studio & Gym in Tampa & Santa Monica
data.text:
Alisha

Stations Instructor

Home State: Connecticut

Adopted Habitat: anywhere that a body of water is nearby :) but Maryland has my heart forevaaaa.

Proudest Accomplishment: deciding to pack up my car in 2019 to move from Maryland to Florida with nothing + no one but successfully creating a fulfilling career and life from scratch.

Strangest Accomplishment: getting 400+ hops on my pogo stick unbroken

Favorite Food: I love ALL food but if I have to choose my favorite...it's the holiday trifecta of macaroni + cheese, collard greens, and candied yams.

Favorite Music: R+B, Afrobeats, and honestly, anything I can twerk to.

Mantra/Favorite Quotes: Every day may not be good but there is something good in every day.

Other Fun Facts: I was a D1 Track and Field Athlete, a two-time High Jump Champ in the America East. My first time flying was to compete in the High Jump and Javelin at the Florida Relays. I have 7 siblings, I can juggle, and I LOVE climbing trees.

Training & Certifications: B.S. in Sociology, OPEX CCP, FRCms, PPSC + CFOL1

Alex

VP Campus Operations

Adopted Habitat: Tampa

Proudest Accomplishment: Being a dad...finally a reason to tell dad jokes!

Favorite Food: Pizza...and coffee

Favorite Music: All of it!

Mantra/Favorite Quotes: It's easier to go down a hill than up it but the view is much better at the top - Henry Ward Beecher

Alex

Assistant General Manager - Tampa + Stations Instructor

Home State: Florida

Favorite Food: Sushi & Avocado Toast

Favorite Music: Mash ups, remixes..basically everything from Lil' Jon Essentials, pop, modern country etc.

Mantra/Favorite Quotes: Health is Wealth. Work hard play hard. Do whatever makes YOU happy!

Other Fun Facts: I started coaching full time & managing gyms at 24 years old. I grew up playing soccer, tennis & volleyball competitively. So naturally, I played every single intramural sport offered in college!

Training & Certifications: NASM CPT, TRX & currently working on becoming a Certified Corrective Exercise Specialist.
